    "content_hash": "fc9622cb892a86eb",
    "department": "Sales",
    "description": "WHO WE ARE\n\nEma is building the next generation AI technology to empower every employee in the enterprise to be their most creative and productive. Our proprietary tech allows enterprises to delegate most repetitive tasks to Ema, the AI employee. We are founded by ex-Google, Coinbase, Okta executives and serial entrepreneurs. We’ve raised capital from notable investors such as Accel Partners, Naspers, Section32 and a host of prominent Silicon Valley Angels including Sheryl Sandberg (Facebook/Google), Divesh Makan (Iconiq Capital), Jerry Yang (Yahoo), Dustin Moskovitz (Facebook/Asana), David Baszucki (Roblox CEO) and Gokul Rajaram (Doordash, Square, Google).\n\nOur team is a powerhouse of talent, comprising engineers from leading tech companies like Google, Microsoft Research, Facebook, Square/Block, and Coinbase. All our team members hail from top-tier educational institutions such as Stanford, MIT, UC Berkeley, CMU and Indian Institute of Technology.  We’re well funded by the top investors and angels in the world. Ema is based in Silicon Valley and Bangalore, India. This will be a hybrid role where we expect employees to work from the office three days a week.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\nThe ideal candidates will be responsible for identifying, engaging, and qualifying potential customers. You’ll play a pivotal role in expanding our customer base by connecting enterprise organizations with our enterprise sales team. We’re looking for SDRs who can produce, learn quickly, and adapt to a variety of solutions and outreach methods. We want someone who is driven, eager to learn, and willing to put in the time to make Ema successful.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n - To create qualified opportunities for the sales team.\n\n - Use different outreach methods to engage our ICP(LinkedIn, Email sequencing, cold calls.)\n\n - Work closely with marketing, drive attendance to webinars, follow up with attendees, help set up meetings for our sales teams at different events.\n\n - Work closely with sales to help book meetings for targeted accounts\n\n - Own your book of business (Know your metrics, SQL’s value, and assigned solutions)\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Minimum of 3 years of experience in a Sales/Business Development or similar role, ideally in SaaS or technology-driven companies.\n\n - Proven track record of successful lead generation, qualification, and pipeline management.\n\n - Has experience selling platform like products with multiple capabilities\n\n - Familiarity with Hubspot and other sales engagement tools.\n\n - Exceptional verbal and written communication skills.\n\n - Experience in a fast-paced startup environment is a plus.\n\nEma Unlimited is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, or genetics.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
